    "objective": "“the applicability and performance of pharmacokinetic screening in detecting pharmacokinetic interactions between valproic acid and carbamazepine”",
    "covariates": "Tested: WT, AGE, DDVPA, SEX, Comedication (PHB, CBZ) Included: WT, DDVPA, SEX, PHB, CBZ",
    "observations": "The paper describes a simplified PK model. A nonlinear relationship between CL and patient characteristic is found. WT is most important covariate, females show lower VPA CL than males, comedication results in an increase in relative CL. VPA CL is large in younger children but decreases as patients mature, a non-linear relation between and maturing, decreasing CL.",
